---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="FAQ | Frequently Asked Questions - Fusion Victoria"
  description="Your questions answered. Our responses to attacks from left and right. Evidence-based, honest, no spin."
>
  <Header />
  
  <Hero 
    title="Frequently Asked Questions"
    subtitle="Honest Answers to Hard Questions"
  />

  <!-- INTRO -->
  <section class="bg-white py-16 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="bg-magenta-light border-l-4 border-magenta p-8 rounded mb-8">
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Major parties will attack us from left and right. Here's what they'll say, and here's the truth.</p>
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold">We're not afraid of scrutiny. We publish our costings. We show our work. We're building in public.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-light-grey p-6 rounded">
        <p class="font-bold mb-4">Jump to section:</p>
        <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
          {[
            ['Debt & Fiscal Responsibility', '#debt'],
            ['Attacks From the Left', '#left-attacks'],
            ['Attacks From the Right', '#right-attacks'],
            ['General Questions', '#general'],
            ['Electoral Strategy', '#electoral'],
            ['Policy Details', '#policy']
          ].map(([label, href]) => (
            <li><a href={href} class="text-magenta hover:text-mint font-semibold">→ {label}</a></li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DEBT & FISCAL RESPONSIBILITY -->
  <section id="debt" class="bg-light-grey py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-12">Debt & Fiscal Responsibility</h2>
      
      <!-- Q: Blow out debt -->
      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-6">Q: "You'll blow out the debt!"</h3>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-3">The Attack (From Both Sides)</h4>
            <p class="mb-2"><strong>Liberals say:</strong> "Reckless spending will bankrupt Victoria!"</p>
            <p><strong>Labor says:</strong> "Unfunded promises that will explode debt!"</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">The Truth</h4>
            <p class="text-xl font-semibold">Victoria's debt is already $177 billion because they build the wrong things at inflated prices.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Current trajectory (major parties):</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-700">
              <li>• Debt reaches $250B by 2035</li>
              <li>• Debt-to-GSP reaches 32%</li>
              <li>• $9.5B wasted on West Gate Tunnel overruns alone</li>
              <li>• 30% average cost blowouts on major projects</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Fusion trajectory:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-700">
              <li>• Debt peaks at $210B in 2028</li>
              <li>• Debt-to-GSP stabilizes at 25% by 2035</li>
              <li>• Infrastructure waste cut from 30% to 10% (saves $1.5B/year)</li>
              <li>• Revenue-generating assets: Public housing returns 4%, renewables return $280M/year net</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-xl font-semibold italic mt-6 text-magenta">We're not afraid of debt when it builds assets that generate returns. We're afraid of waste, which is what they've been doing.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Q: How do you pay for it -->
      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-6">Q: "How do you actually pay for all this?"</h3>
        
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold mb-6">Three mechanisms: Stop waste, grow revenue, smart investment.</p>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-light-grey p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">Stop the Waste</h4>
            <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">$2.8B/year saved</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1">
              <li>• Infrastructure overruns cut 30%→10%: <strong>$1.5B/year</strong></li>
              <li>• End private hospital tax exemptions: <strong>$1.5B/year</strong></li>
              <li>• Procurement reform: <strong>Redirect savings to public services</strong></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-light-grey p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">Grow the Revenue</h4>
            <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">$2B/year additional</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1">
              <li>• Land tax transition (properties >$1M): <strong>$800M/year</strong></li>
              <li>• State renewables net returns: <strong>$280M/year</strong></li>
              <li>• Public housing rent: <strong>$1.2B/year</strong> (once built)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-light-grey p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">Smart Investment</h4>
            <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Assets that pay for themselves</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1">
              <li>• Public housing: 4% direct return, 8% with externalities</li>
              <li>• Renewables: $280M/year profit</li>
              <li>• Transport: Reduces congestion costs, enables economic activity</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[var(--magenta)]/10 p-6 rounded border-2 border-magenta">
          <p class="text-lg"><strong>Total savings + revenue:</strong> $4.8B/year</p>
          <p class="text-lg"><strong>Total new spending:</strong> $3.9B/year healthcare + $1.5B/year transport operational + other programs</p>
          <p class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mt-2">Net impact: Sustainable fiscal path with debt-to-GSP declining to 25%</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- LEFT ATTACKS -->
  <section id="left-attacks" class="bg-white py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-12">Attacks From the Left (Labor, Greens)</h2>
      
      <!-- Q: Neoliberals -->
      <div class="bg-light-grey p-8 rounded-lg mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-6">Q: "You're just neoliberals / corporate shills / crypto-Liberals!"</h3>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-3">The Attack</h4>
            <p class="mb-2"><strong>Greens say:</strong> "You support markets and economic growth, therefore you're right-wing!"</p>
            <p><strong>Labor says:</strong> "You'll split the progressive vote and let Liberals win!"</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">The Truth</h4>
            <p class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">We're building 50,000 public homes. Criminalizing wage theft. Supporting UBI. Pushing 100% renewables by 2030. End private hospital tax breaks.</p>
            <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta">That's more left-wing than Labor's actual policies.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lg mb-4">The difference is we're not afraid to use markets where they work, and reject them where they don't:</p>
        
        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-6">
          <li><strong>Housing:</strong> Market has failed. Build public housing at scale.</li>
          <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> For-profit hospitals get tax breaks while public system fails. End the exemptions, fund public.</li>
          <li><strong>Energy:</strong> Market won't build fast enough. State builds 2GW renewables, proves profitability, market follows.</li>
          <li><strong>Transport:</strong> Obviously public good. Build it, fund it, run it publicly.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold italic text-magenta">We're pragmatic progressives. We use whatever tools work to improve people's lives.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Q: Land Value Tax hurts renters -->
      <div class="bg-light-grey p-8 rounded-lg mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-6">Q: "Land Value Tax hurts renters / working families!"</h3>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-3">The Attack</h4>
            <p><strong>Labor/Greens say:</strong> "Property taxes get passed on to renters. You're hurting the people you claim to help!"</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">The Truth</h4>
            <p class="text-xl font-semibold">LVT can't be passed on to renters. That's not how land economics works.</p>
            <p class="mt-2"><strong>Why:</strong> Landlords already charge maximum rent the market will bear. If they could charge more, they already would be.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Who pays:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1">
              <li>• Our LVT increase targets properties valued >$1M</li>
              <li>• That's not working families' homes</li>
              <li>• That's investors with multiple properties and commercial landholders</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Who benefits:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1">
              <li>• 50,000 public homes funded partly by this revenue</li>
              <li>• Lower land speculation = lower purchase prices over time</li>
              <li>• More efficient land use = more housing supply</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-xl font-semibold italic mt-6 text-magenta">Every serious economist from Adam Smith to Henry George to modern Nobel Prize winners agrees: LVT is the most efficient tax.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Q: Splitting the vote -->
      <div class="bg-light-grey p-8 rounded-lg mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-6">Q: "You're splitting the progressive vote!"</h3>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-3">The Attack</h4>
            <p><strong>Labor says:</strong> "Every vote for Fusion is a vote for the Liberals! You'll let them win!"</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">The Truth</h4>
            <p class="text-xl font-semibold">We have preferential voting. Your vote isn't wasted even if we don't win.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">How it works:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1">
            <li>• You put Fusion first</li>
            <li>• If we don't win, your vote flows to your second preference</li>
            <li>• Liberals don't benefit unless you preference them (don't do that)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">What your Fusion vote does:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1">
            <li>• Sends message that corporate-funded major parties are losing support</li>
            <li>• Forces Labor/Greens to explain why they won't match our policies</li>
            <li>• Builds long-term movement (Greens started with 2.8% in 1996, now they're kingmakers)</li>
            <li>• If we win seats, gives us platform to expose waste and force change</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <p class="text-xl font-semibold italic mt-6 text-magenta">Labor had 12 years to build public housing, fix transport, criminalise wage theft. They didn't. They won't. Vote for what you actually want.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RIGHT ATTACKS -->
  <section id="right-attacks" class="bg-light-grey py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-12">Attacks From the Right (Liberals, One Nation)</h2>
      
      <!-- Q: Socialists -->
      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-6">Q: "You're socialists / communists / will destroy the economy!"</h3>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-3">The Attack</h4>
            <p class="mb-2"><strong>Liberals say:</strong> "Public housing is socialism! You'll crash the economy!"</p>
            <p><strong>One Nation says:</strong> "You're left-wing extremists!"</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">The Truth</h4>
            <p class="text-xl font-semibold">We're capitalists who think markets work better when everyone has a foundation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[var(--mint)]/10 p-6 rounded mb-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Public housing isn't socialism. It's smart investment:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1">
            <li>• Costs $25B to build 50,000 homes</li>
            <li>• Generates $1.2B/year in rent revenue (4% return)</li>
            <li>• Saves $450M/year in homelessness/health/justice costs</li>
            <li>• Construction creates 25,000 jobs during build</li>
            <li>• Economic multiplier: Every $1 spent generates $1.80-$2.20 in economic activity</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 font-semibold">This is how Singapore built prosperity: 80% homeownership through public housing. Not socialism - smart capitalism.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-xl font-semibold italic text-magenta">We're not seizing private property. We're building public assets that generate returns and create a stable consumer base for private business.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Q: Immigration -->
      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-6">Q: "Immigration is the real problem!"</h3>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-3">The Attack</h4>
            <p class="mb-2"><strong>One Nation says:</strong> "Stop immigration! Immigrants take our jobs and houses!"</p>
            <p><strong>Some Liberals dog-whistle:</strong> "Population growth outpacing infrastructure..."</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">The Truth</h4>
            <p class="text-xl font-semibold">Immigrants don't take your jobs or houses. Your boss steals your wages. Developers don't build public housing. Blame the right people.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-magenta-solid text-white p-6 rounded">
          <p class="font-bold text-xl mb-3 text-mint">Our framing: Workers vs Exploiters</p>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Blame:</strong> Property investors, corporate tax dodgers, wage-stealing bosses, political donors</p>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Never:</strong> Migrants, welfare recipients, other workers</p>
          <p class="text-xl font-bold mt-4">We're all working people being ripped off</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Q: UBI makes people lazy -->
      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-6">Q: "Universal Basic Income will make people lazy!"</h3>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-3">The Attack</h4>
            <p><strong>Liberals/One Nation say:</strong> "Why would anyone work if you give them free money? Welfare queens!"</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-6 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">The Truth</h4>
            <p class="text-xl font-semibold">Every UBI trial shows people keep working. They just have power to refuse exploitative jobs.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Evidence from trials (Finland, Kenya, Canada):</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-6">
          <li>• Employment rates stay same or increase slightly</li>
          <li>• People retrain, start businesses, care for family</li>
          <li>• Mental health improves, domestic violence decreases</li>
          <li>• Kids' educational outcomes improve (stable housing)</li>
          <li>• People don't stop working - they stop accepting shit jobs for shit pay</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 rounded">
          <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Also: You already subsidize corporate welfare:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1">
            <li>• $300B in negative gearing and capital gains tax discounts over 10 years</li>
            <li>• Billions in fossil fuel subsidies</li>
            <li>• Private hospital tax exemptions: $1.5B/year</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-xl font-bold mt-4 text-blue-700">We give welfare to property investors and corporations. Why not people?</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GENERAL QUESTIONS -->
  <section id="general" class="bg-white py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-12">General Questions</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-light-grey p-8 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Q: "Who funds Fusion?"</h3>
          <p class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">People. Not corporations. Not unions. Not property developers.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>• <strong>Individual donations only</strong> (capped at $1,500/year per person)</li>
            <li>• <strong>No corporate donations</strong></li>
            <li>• <strong>No union donations</strong> (though we support workers' rights)</li>
            <li>• <strong>No property developer donations</strong></li>
            <li>• <strong>Quarterly disclosure</strong> (not just annually)</li>
            <li>• <strong>All donors over $500 published</strong></li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-xl font-semibold italic mt-4 text-magenta">We can fight for you because we're funded by you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-light-grey p-8 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Q: "Are you just another protest vote that won't achieve anything?"</h3>
          <p class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Every movement starts somewhere. Greens won 2.8% in 1996. Now they're kingmakers.</p>
          <p class="mb-4"><strong>Even if we don't form government, we force change:</strong></p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li>• Every vote sends message that corporate-funded parties are losing support</li>
            <li>• If we win seats, we get Question Time to expose waste</li>
            <li>• We get budget committee positions to investigate</li>
            <li>• We get media platform to shift debate</li>
            <li>• We get balance-of-power leverage if no majority</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-xl font-semibold italic text-magenta">The ideas matter more than who gets credit.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-light-grey p-8 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Q: "Where can I see your full costings?"</h3>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4"><a href="https://fusionparty.org.au/costings" class="text-magenta underline hover:text-mint">fusionparty.org.au/costings</a></p>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>What we publish:</strong></p>
          <ul class="space-y-1">
            <li>• Line-by-line budget breakdown</li>
            <li>• Funding sources for every commitment</li>
            <li>• Methodology and assumptions</li>
            <li>• Peer review by independent economists</li>
            <li>• Comparison to major party costings (or lack thereof)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ELECTORAL STRATEGY -->
  <section id="electoral" class="bg-light-grey py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-12">Electoral Strategy</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Q: "Which seats are you contesting?"</h3>
          <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Target electorates (confirmed):</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>• <a href="/electorate-melton" class="text-magenta hover:underline">Melton</a> - Melton Line electrification priority</li>
            <li>• <a href="/electorate-pakenham" class="text-magenta hover:underline">Pakenham</a> - Clyde Line duplication priority</li>
            <li>• <a href="/electorate-sunbury" class="text-magenta hover:underline">Sunbury</a> - Electrification and bus network priority</li>
            <li>• <a href="/electorate-werribee" class="text-magenta hover:underline">Werribee</a> - Wyndham Vale parking and hospital priority</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Q: "How should I preference?"</h3>
          <p class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">We don't tell you how to vote beyond "put Fusion first." But here's our thinking:</p>
          <div class="bg-[var(--mint)]/10 p-6 rounded">
            <p class="font-bold mb-2">After Fusion, preference based on:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1">
              <li>• Who's most likely to adopt our policies</li>
              <li>• Who takes least corporate donations</li>
              <li>• Who's published real costings (not just promises)</li>
              <li>• Who's fighting for workers vs donors</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- POLICY DETAILS -->
  <section id="policy" class="bg-white py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-12">Policy Details</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-light-grey p-8 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Q: "Why 50,000 homes specifically?"</h3>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <p class="font-bold mb-2">Based on actual need:</p>
              <ul class="space-y-1">
                <li>• 116,000 people on public housing waitlist</li>
                <li>• Average wait time: 6+ years</li>
                <li>• Victoria currently builds ~500 public homes/year</li>
                <li>• At current rate, would take 232 years to clear waitlist</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-bold mb-2">12,500 homes/year for 4 years:</p>
              <ul class="space-y-1">
                <li>• Clears ~43% of current waitlist</li>
                <li>• Accommodates ongoing population growth</li>
                <li>• Matches construction industry capacity with ramp-up</li>
